    <header>
      <h1>API Documentation</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="endpoint">
      <h2>About qrcodeGen v2 API</h2>
      <p class="p"><b>qrcodeGen</b> is a qrcode generating API, request can be sent via CURL, a Browser, Postman or any other API client, and also example illustrated below is in CURL</p>
      <h2>qrcodeGen v2 features</h2>
      <p class="p">
        <b>qrcodeGen</b> has been updated and new cool fetures has been added to it, generating of qrcodes based on your needs be it text, url, a wifi network information and others, also support for external link has been added, meaning you can generate qrcode image links and use them externally e.g your HTML img tag.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h2>GET /api/v2/qrcode/gen</h2>
        <p class="p"><strong>Description:</strong> Generates a qrcode image with the text provided in request body.</p>
        <h2>List of query options for this endpoint</h2>
        <h3><code>?type</code></h3>
        <p>States the type of qrcode you want to generate</p>
        <p><b>Example:</b> <code class="code">/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=url</code></p>
        <h3>The <code>?type</code> options</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <details>
            <summary><code class="code">?type=text</code></summary>
            <p class="d">Declears a text qrcode</p>
            <p><b>Example:</b> <code class="code">/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=url&text=Hello-World</code></p>
            <p>Returns the generated qrcode on the webpage</p>
        </details>
        </li>
          <li>
            <details>
            <summary><code class="code">?type=url</code></summary>
            <p class="d">Declears a url qrcode</p>
            <p><b>Example:</b> <code class="code">/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=url&url=www.google.com</code></p>
            <p>Returns the generated qrcode on the webpage</p>
        </details>
        </li>
          <li>
            <details>
            <summary><code class="code">?type=wifi</code></summary>
            <p class="d">Declears a wifi network information qrcode</p>
            <p><b>Example:</b> <code class="code">/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=wifi&wifiname=Aitel_mifi_box108&wifipassword=9aug56gy</code></p>
            <p>Returns the generated qrcode on the webpage</p>
        </details>
        </li>
          <li>
            <details>
            <summary><code class="code">?type=vcard</code></summary>
            <p class="d">Declears a business card information qrcode</p>
            <p><b>Example:</b> <code class="code">/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=vcard&companyname=Demi_Lounge&companyaddress=No.2_Cray_Street&companyemail=demilounge@gmail.com</code></p>
            <p>Returns the generated qrcode on the webpage</p>
        </details>
        </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="request">
            <h3>Request</h3>
            <p><b>GET</b></p>
            <p class="code">curl "https://qrcode-gen-pad.onrender.com/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=url&text=Hello-World"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="response">
            <h3>Response</h3>
            <p class="code">HTTP/1.1 201 Created</p>
        </div>
        <p class="p">If the request was made with your broswer, Postman any API client of your choice, it renders the qrcode image</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h2>How to generate a qrcode image to be used externally</h2>
        <p class="p">It still uses the same <code class="code">?type</code> query</p>
        <div class="request">
            <h3>Request</h3>
            <p class="code">curl "https://qrcode-gen-pad.onrender.com/api/v2/qrcode/gen?type=external&data=Arandomdata"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="response">
            <h3>Response</h3>
            <p class="code">HTTP/1.1 201 Created</p>
        </div>
        <h3>Json response returned</h3>
        <div class="response">
          <p class="code">
  {
    status: 'success',
    message: 'qrcode image generated, the below link can be used externally',
    imgurl: `https://qrcode-gen-pad.onrender.com/api/v2/qrcode/image/qrcode_ju7s.png`
}
        </code></p>
        </div>
    <h3>How to use in HTML img tag</h3>
        <div class="response">
          <p class="code">
< img src="https://qrcode-gen-pad.onrender.com/api/v2/qrcode/image/qrcode_ju7s.png" alt="qrcode image" >
          </p>
        </div>
